<mapping> The <mapping>
        tag represents a complex data type.


You can use nested <mapping> (and nested
        <element> with <element> tags)
        to represent the full complexity of the structure. Bear in mind that
        what you are creating will be mapped to an associative array that will
        be passed in via
        PEAR_PackageFileMaintainer::setOptions().

        <mapping name="option_name">
    <element key="key_name" value="key_val"/>
    <element key="key_name" value="key_val"/>
</mapping>


Available mappings and they structures:




deps (optional) see PEAR_PackageFileManager::addDependency()
            for more info


              Attributes for deps

              &taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;



                channel

                String

                Channel name, from package is.

                &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

                &attributes.required.yes;




                name

                String

                Package name in channel.

                &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

                &attributes.required.yes;




                version

                String

                Minimal version.

                &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

                &attributes.required.yes;




                max

                String

                Maximum version.

                Same as
                version.

                &attributes.required.no;




                recommended

                String

                Recommended version.

                Same as
                version.

                &attributes.required.no;






